	<br/>
	<p>Network analyzing tools in the <a href="http://www.linkgroup.hu/">LINK-group</a>:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><i>Turbine:</i> a versatile program package for the analysis of network dynamics, including the effect of single and multiple perturbations.<a href="http://www.linkgroup.hu/Turbine.php">	Visit Turbine</a></li>
		<li><i>NetworGame:</i> a tool for the analysis of a large variety of spatial games on model and real world networks including the option for individual starting strategies for any network nodes.<a href="http://www.linkgroup.hu/NetworGame.php">	Visit NetworGame</a></li>
		<li><i>ModuLand:</i> Analysis of complex, real-world networksup to several million nodes, identification of key nodes and prediction of behavior.<a href="http://www.linkgroup.hu/modules.php">	Visit ModuLand</a></li>
	</ul>
	<br />
	<p>Network-related tools in the <a href="http://netbiol.elte.hu/index.php/en/">NetBiol network biology group</a>:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><i>Signalink:</i> A multi-layered signaling and regulatory resource based on manual curation and integration to focus on cross-talks, multi-pathway proteins and signal flow regulation<a href="http://signalink.org/">	Visit Signalink</a></li>
		<li><i>Autophagy Regulation:</i> Systems-level resource of autophagy regulation, including transcriptional, post-transcriptional regulatory mechanisms and signaling pahways.<a href="http://arn.elte.hu/">	Visit Autophagy Regulation</a></li>
		<li><i>NRF2-ome:</i> Manually curated, predicted and collected systems-level resource of NRF2.<a href="http://nrf2.elte.hu">	Visit NRF2-ome</a></li>
		<li><i>Cross-talk endosomes:</i> List of endosome-associated scaffold proteins and their cross-talk mediating properties.<a href="http://netbiol.elte.hu/endosome">	Visit Cross-talk endosomes</a></li>
		<li><i>PathwayLinker:</i> Webservice for analyzing the signaling pathway memberships of proteins and their interactors for experiment design and evaluation<a href="http://pathwaylinker.org/"> 	Visit PathwayLinker</a></li>
		<li><i>Signalog:</i> Tool for orthology based identification of novel signaling proteins<a href="http://signalink.org/signalog">	Visit Signalog</a></li>
	</ul>
	
